          <p class='first-para'>
            We have had a most interesting debate. I think it has illuminated in admirable fashion both the Bill and the difficulties that arise from it&#x2014;between those of us who think that sex is not a lifestyle choice that we make for ourselves, but a choice that is made above and beyond us and is inherent in our biological nature. Sex, some of us think, is not a psychological
            
            <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_23gc' title='Col. 23GC &mdash; HL Deb 13 January 2004 vol 657 c23GC' name='column_23gc' href='#column_23gc' rel='bookmark'>23GC</a>
